# Testing & Quality (SCP)

**No untested code. No broken flows. No shipping errors.**

Standards: [Engineering Standards §6–7](V2.0/docs/00-meta/engineering-standards.md) · [Vol 13 Testing](V2.0/docs/13-testing/README.md)

## Testing is mandatory

- **Every change** includes tests: new code → new tests; bug fix → regression test
- Run relevant tests after implementation; **fix all failures before finishing** — do not leave red tests
- **Full flow coverage** for the feature: happy path + auth failure + validation errors + tenant isolation where applicable
- Critical paths (auth, payments, checkout, tenant RLS): 100% branch coverage required

| Layer | Tool | When |
|-------|------|------|
| PHP Actions / Domain | Pest unit | Every use case |
| HTTP API | Pest feature | Every route (200/201, 403, 422) |
| Tenant isolation | Pest + PostgreSQL | Any data access change |
| React / Next.js | Vitest + component tests | Non-trivial UI logic |
| User flows | Playwright | Checkout, CRUD, auth flows |

## Zero broken code policy

- **Do not mark work complete** if tests fail, linter errors remain, or the app throws
- **Backend:** no uncaught exceptions in normal flows; no HTTP 500 for expected cases — return 4xx with Problem Details
- **Frontend:** no white screens — every route must render loading, empty, error, and success states (Vol 4)
- **Frontend:** no unhandled promise rejections; error boundaries on app shells
- Fix **root cause**, not suppress errors with empty catch blocks or `@ts-ignore` without justification

## Before finishing a task

1. Run tests for touched packages (`composer test`, targeted PHPUnit, Vitest as applicable) — **in background** (see `.cursor/rules/background-commands-default.mdc`)
2. Poll with `Await` before reporting pass/fail; fix failures before finishing
3. Verify the user flow end-to-end when changing a feature (manual or E2E if available)
4. Confirm no new PHPStan/Pint/ESLint violations in changed files

## Test execution (background required)

- **Always** run `composer test`, `vendor/bin/phpunit`, Playwright, and CI-equivalent commands with `block_until_ms: 0` (background).
- Continue implementation or other work while tests run; use `Await` with a completion pattern (`OK (`, `FAILURES!`, `ERRORS!`) before marking work done.
- Report final pass/fail counts from the terminal output file — do not ask the user to click "Run in background".
- Foreground tests only when the user explicitly says "wait for output", "run in foreground", or "block until done".

See `.cursor/rules/background-commands-default.mdc` for Shell defaults.

## Build & install commands

**Do not run build or install unless the user explicitly requests it in the current message.**

Forbidden without explicit request:

- `npm install` / `npm ci` / `npm run build` / `npm run dev` / `yarn` / `pnpm`
- Docusaurus build or dev server
- `composer install` (unless user asked to set up dependencies)

Allowed: `composer test`, `vendor/bin/phpunit`, targeted lint on changed files, reading/running single test files — **background by default** (see `background-commands-default.mdc`).

See `.cursor/rules/no-npm-build.mdc`.

## Definition of done

- [ ] Tests written and **passing**
- [ ] Full feature flow tested (not only unit-isolated happy path)
- [ ] No 500 errors in normal operation
- [ ] No white screen / crash on frontend routes touched
- [ ] Task acceptance criteria from spec verified
